 proximity to major sea lanes of communication. This book carefully maps out the tensions, contradictions, and implications of the use of preman organizations in the realization of Indonesia’s efforts to be a truly democratic civil society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aSecurity. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102456140uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981501189040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789815011890423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789815011890/original  a978-3-11-102456-1  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles